Privacy Policy for Quick2TV (Chrome Extension)
Last Updated: 2025-02-12

------------------------------------------------
1. Overview

Quick2TV is a lightweight Chrome extension designed to open TradingView charts quickly and provide helpful search suggestions.
This extension is built with user privacy as the highest priority.
Quick2TV does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal data.
------------------------------------------------
2. Data Collection

Quick2TV does NOT collect any personal information such as:
- Names
- Email addresses
- Browsing history
- IP addresses
- Trading activity
- Financial information
- Device identifiers
- Cookies

The extension does not include analytics, advertisements, or trackers.
------------------------------------------------
3. Local Storage Usage

Quick2TV uses Chrome Storage only to store user preferences locally, including:

Dark mode preference

Search history (stock symbols)

These values:

Stay only on the user's local browser

Are not sent to any server

Are fully under user control (can be cleared anytime via Chrome)

Quick2TV does not access, read, or modify any other browser data.
------------------------------------------------
4. Permissions Explanation

The extension requests minimal permissions:

tabs

Used only to open TradingView charts in a new tab.

storage

Used only to locally save UI preferences and search history.

Quick2TV does not use these permissions to monitor, collect, or track any browsing activity.
------------------------------------------------
5. Third-Party Services

Quick2TV loads TradingView chart pages when opening a symbol.
This is equivalent to a user manually visiting:

https://www.tradingview.com/chart/

Quick2TV does not inject scripts into trading websites nor send user data to TradingView.

Please refer to TradingView’s own privacy policy regarding their website:
https://www.tradingview.com/privacy-policy/
------------------------------------------------
6. Data Sharing

Quick2TV does NOT share data with:

Third parties

Advertisers

Analytics providers

External servers

The developer
------------------------------------------------
7. User Control

Users may clear all Quick2TV-related stored data anytime via:

Chrome Extensions → Quick2TV → "Clear data"

Chrome Settings → Privacy → Clear browsing data → "Hosted app data"

No other actions are required.
------------------------------------------------
8. Children’s Privacy

Quick2TV does not target or collect data from children under 13 years of age.
------------------------------------------------
9. Policy Updates

Any future updates to this policy will be published publicly, and the version date will be updated.
------------------------------------------------
10. Contact

If you have any privacy-related questions, please contact the developer:

